4/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large-800x1000.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large-800x1000.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large-96x120.jpeg 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large-768x960.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-13-Large.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-800x533.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-9-Large.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large-800x640.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large-800x640.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large-297x238.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large-768x614.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-11-Large.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large-800x640.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large-800x640.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large-297x238.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large-768x614.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Finished-Bike-at-Recycling-Center-8-Large.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The theme didn’t stop there. The build includes recycled rubber grips by Björn Bikes, recycled aluminum components by Velocity, White Industries, and PAUL Components, a headtube badge made from leftover scrap metal by Jen Green, an old B72 saddle chassis that has been re-upholstered by Jerry Smith, and even some custom bags made from an old Sierra Nevada billboard by Outershell!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-800x533.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-Velocity-4-Large.jpeg 888w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large-800x1000.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large-800x1000.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large-96x120.jpeg 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large-768x960.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-9-Large.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large-800x1000.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large-800x1000.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large-96x120.jpeg 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large-768x960.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Process-White-Industries-7-Large.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As Travis from PAUL Component Engineering puts it, “We don’t think there are necessarily any easy or final answers when talking about sustainability and environmental thoughtfulness in the bicycle industry, but the first step is asking questions, and the second step is trying new things.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stop by the Sierra Nevada beer tent to see the bike at the show, and <a href=\"https://action.outdooralliance.org/a/sierra-recycler-giveaway\" target=\"_blank\">donate $5 or more to Outdoor Alliance</a> by May 31st for a chance to win the Sierra Recycler. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sierra-recycler-custom-mountain-bike-sea-otter-raffle/\">The Sierra Recycler is Built from Recycled &amp; Reused Parts: You Can Win it at Sea Otter!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4222683e3c1f6b4d9c0372e1718673247bfcf5ea804fc920049dacca1a1ddabe","category":"Cycling"}